The **Senior Programmer** performs a variety of programming assignments requiring knowledge of established programming procedures and data processing while also, maintaining and modifying software programs. Designs, develops, tests and implements software for clients to improve business efficiency and productivity.

**Requirements:**

* Bachelor’s Degree in Information Systems, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or related areas;
* Minimum of five (5\) years of experience in the complete programming cycle, including: collection and analysis of requirements, design of the architecture, administer tests, data management and documentation for the creation of new systems;
* Strong knowledge in Visual Studio, C\#, MS SQL, T\-SQL, Asp.net, MVC.net, ENTITY FRAMEWORK, SQL, MS Reporting Services, MS Integration Services, SharePoint, CSS, GIT, JavaScript, jQuery, HTML, REDMINE, BOOTSTRAP, Window FORMS, XML, CSharp\+, SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS);
* Additional Knowledge (PYTHON, MYSQL, Node.js, React.JS, Laravel), Mobile Development is a plus;
* Knowledge of scrum and agile software development methodologies is a plus;
* Knowledge of virtualization and cloud services concepts is also a plus;
* Fully bilingual (English and Spanish)
